---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Configuration · Squeezy"
  description="Squeezy configuration precedence, provider defaults, credentials, and local inspection commands."
  activeDoc="/docs/config/"
  eyebrow="configuration"
  heading="Configuration is layered and inspectable."
  lead="Squeezy keeps provider choice, model profile, permissions, sandboxing, telemetry, graph settings, and session behavior in one typed configuration model."
>
  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Precedence</h2>
    <p>From highest to lowest precedence, Squeezy resolves settings from CLI flags, environment variables, the nearest project `squeezy.toml`, user `~/.squeezy/settings.toml`, and built-in defaults.</p>
    <div class="doc-card-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">inspect</span>
        <h3>See the merged config</h3>
        <pre><code>squeezy config inspect</code></pre>
        <p>Sensitive values are redacted before display.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">doctor</span>
        <h3>Check runtime readiness</h3>
        <pre><code>squeezy doctor</code></pre>
        <p>Doctor reports config sources, provider credential state, repo profile, session store, and sandbox availability.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Provider example</h2>
    <p>Provider defaults are stored as names and settings. Secret token values stay in environment variables, macOS Keychain, AWS credentials, or the provider's own local runtime.</p>
    <pre><code>[model]
provider = "openai"
profile = "balanced"
model = ""

[providers.openai]
api_key_env = "OPENAI_API_KEY"

[permissions]
web = "ask"
shell = "ask"</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Why it matters for cost</h2>
    <p>Configuration controls the model profile, context limit hints, tool budgets, schema loading, web permission policy, telemetry opt-out, and shell sandbox behavior. Those settings decide when Squeezy can use local evidence and when it is allowed to spend provider context.</p>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
